pproaches, including, for example, multiple streams, advocacy coalition, punctuated equilibrium and veto player approaches. The chapters explore how the approaches can be adapted and transferred to the study of foreign policy and point to the challenges this entails. By establishing a critical dialogue between approaches in public policy and research on foreign policy, the main contribution of the book is to broaden the available theoretical ‘toolkit’ in foreign policy analysis.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aInternational relations. 0aPolitical planning. 0aPolitical science. 4aInternational Relations 2020. 4aPolitical Studies 2020. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Comparative Politics.2bisacsh  aadvocacy coalition.  aforeign policy.  amultiple streams.  apublic policy.  apunctuated equilibrium.  aveto player.1 aAnsell, Christopher, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBiedenkopf, Katja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlavoukos, Spyros, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrummer, Klaus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrummer, Klaus, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHarnisch, Sebastian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarnisch, Sebastian, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHicks, Katherine C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJoly, Jeroen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaarbo, Juliet, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMattelaer, Alexander, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOppermann, Kai, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/rel